  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2020-01-28",
    "date": "2020-02-27T20:50:42Z",
    "text": "Helping Emergency Responders Overcome Act of 2020 or the HERO Act of 2020\n\nThis bill establishes a series of programs relating to the behavioral health of public-safety officers (e.g., law-enforcement officers, firefighters, ambulance crew members, and 911 operators). For example, the bill establishes (1) a public-safety officer suicide-reporting system at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, and (2) a grant program for peer-support behavioral health and wellness programs within fire departments and emergency medical services agencies."
  },
